<title>USA: FDA approves CardioVascular Lynx catheter.</title>
<headline>FDA approves CardioVascular Lynx catheter.</headline>
<dateline>IRVINE, Calif. 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>CardioVascular Dynamics Inc said the U.S. Food and Drug Administration approved its Lynx catheters.  </p>
<p>The Lynx catheters use CardioVascular's Focus technology that inflates a balloon to correct a atherosclerosis, a condition that blocks blood flow in the coronary arteries.</p>
<p>Unlike conventional balloon angioplasty devices, which direct dilation force over the entire length of the balloon, the Lynx catheters focus the force more directly to the lesion site, helping spare the surrounding arterial wall from damage, CardioVascular said.</p>
